# Autonomous Execution Default

When the user gives an implementation request, execute it end-to-end without asking for routine confirmation.

## Default Behavior

- Treat direct requests as approval to proceed.
- Run needed edits, commands, validation, and follow-up fixes in one flow.
- Prefer action over proposal when requirements are already clear.

## When Questions Are Still Allowed

- Ask only if a true blocker exists (missing credentials, missing external access, destructive risk, or conflicting requirements).
- If multiple valid options exist, pick a reasonable default and proceed; report what was chosen.
- Do not ask "Should I continue?" after partial progress unless user safety or data loss is involved.

## Progress and Reporting

- Provide short progress updates while working.
- At completion, report outcomes, remaining risks, and concrete next steps.
- If some work cannot be completed, state exactly what is blocked and continue with all unblocked tasks.
